英国","Kent, England":"英国肯特","lifeSummary":"当Thomas de Bois于1280年出生在英国英格兰肯特迪亞爾时，他的父亲Edmund de Bois38岁，母亲Mary35岁。他于1307年与Margaretta Bonyngton结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1311年在英国肯特享年31岁。"},"hr":{"1280–1311":"1280.–1311.","1282–Male":"1282–preminuo","1285–Female":"1285–preminula","1282–1311":"1282–1311.","1307–1362":"1307.–1362","1243–Male":"1243–preminuo","1245–1284":"1245–1284.","1311":"1311.","1245":"1245","1243":"1243","about 1279":"oko 1279.","1362":"1362","1285":"1285","1284":"1284.","1282":"1282","1280":"1280.","1307":"1307.","1290":"1290","Deal, Kent, England":"Deal, Kent, Engleska, United Kingdom","Goodnestone, Kent, England":"Goodnestone, Kent, England","England":"England","Kent, England":"Kent, England"},"cs":{"1280–1311":"1280–1311","1282–Male":"1282–Zesnulý","1285–Female":"1285–Zesnulá","1282–1311":"1282–1311","1307–1362":"1307–1362","1243–Male":"1243–Zesnulý","1245–1284":"1245–1284","1311":"1311","1245":"1245","1243":"1243","about 1279":"okolo 1279","1362":"1362","1285":"1285","1284":"1284","1282":"1282","1280":"1280","1307":"1307","1290":"1290","Deal, Kent, England":"Deal, Kent, Anglie, United Kingdom","Goodnestone, Kent, England":"Goodnestone, Kent, Anglie","England":"Anglie","Kent, England":"Kent, Anglie"},"da":{"1280–1311":"1280–1311","1282–Male":"1282–Afdød","1285–Female":"1285–Afdød","1282–1311":"1282–1311","1307–1362":"1307–1362","1243–Male":"1243–Afdød","1245–1284":"1245–1284","1311":"1311","1245":"1245","1243":"1243","about 1279":"omkring 1279","1362":"1362","1285":"1285","1284":"1284","1282":"1282","1280":"1280","1307":"1307","1290":"1290","Deal, Kent, England":"Deal, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Goodnestone, Kent, England":"Goodnestone, Kent, England","England":"England","Kent, England":"Kent, England"},"nl":{"1280–1311":"1280–1311","1282–Male":"1282–Overleden","1285–Female":"1285–Overleden","1282–1311":"1282–1311","1307–1362":"1307–1362","1243–Male":"1243–Overleden","1245–1284":"1245–1284","1311":"1311","1245":"1245","1243":"1243","about 1279":"circa 1279","1362":"1362","1285":"1285","1284":"1284","1282":"1282","1280":"1280","1307":"1307","1290":"1290","Deal, Kent, England":"Deal, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Goodnestone, Kent, England":"Goodnestone, Kent, England","England":"England","Kent, England":"Kent, England"},"en":{"1280–1311":"1280–1311","1282–Male":"1282–Deceased","1285–Female":"1285–Deceased","1282–1311":"1282–1311","1307–1362":"1307–1362","1243–Male":"1243–Deceased","1245–1284":"1245–1284","1311":"1311","1245":"1245","1243":"1243","about 1279":"about 1279","1362":"1362","1285":"1285","1284":"1284","1282":"1282","1280":"1280","1307":"1307","1290":"1290","Deal, Kent, England":"Deal, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Goodnestone, Kent, England":"Goodnestone, Kent, England","England":"England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Bois","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alcide, Antoine, Donat, Marcel, Ovide, Ovila, Raoul, Serge.","French: topographic name for someone living or working in a wood, from (Old) French <i>bois</i> ‘wood’ (from Late Latin <i>boscum</i> ‘bush, shrub, undergrowth’, of ancient Germanic origin), or a habitational name from (Le) Bois, the name of several places in various parts of France. This surname is also found in Haiti. Compare   Debois   and the most frequent French form   Dubois  . Compare also   Boie  ,   Boies  , and   Boyce  .","English: variant of   Boyce   and   Boyes  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dubois","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Armand, Normand, Jacques, Pierre, Fernand, Marcel, Emile, Lucien, Michel, Alain, Luc.","French, Walloon, and English (of French Huguenot origin): topographic name, with fused preposition and definite article <i>du</i> ‘from the’, for someone living or working in a wood (see   Bois  ), or a habitational name for someone from any of several places in various parts of France and in Belgium (Wallonia) named Le Bois. This is the most frequent surname in Wallonia. It is also found in the Flemish part of Belgium, the Netherlands, Germany, and Haiti. In both England and North America it is sometimes translated into English as   Wood  . Compare   Deboe  ,   Debois  ,   Deboy  ,   Duboise  , and   Dubose  .","History: This surname is listed (in the form <i>Du Bois</i>) in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America. One of the several Huguenot ancestors bearing this name was Chrétien Du Bois from Flanders, whose son, Louis Du Bois (born 1626 in Lille, France, died 1696 in Kingston, NY), was among the Huguenots who founded the town of New Paltz, NY 1675–78."]},{"name":"Boisvert","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Armand, Andre, Donat, Lucien, Jacques, Gaston, Normand, Pierre, Gilles, Herve, Adrien.","French:","topographic name for someone who lived in a dense forest or perhaps a copse of evergreens, from Old French <i>bois</i> ‘wood’ (see   Bois  ) + <i>vert, verd</i> ‘green’."]},{"name":"Boisclair","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Normand, Marcel, Aldege, Alphonse, Arsene, Edmour, Emile, Leopaul, Prudent, Rejean, Remi, Yves.","French: topographic name from Old French <i>bois</i> ‘wood’ (see   Bois  ) + <i>clair</i> ‘clear, light’, or a habitational name from (Le) Bois Clair, the name of several places in various parts of France. This surname is virtually non-existing in France."]},{"name":"Boies","meanings":["Altered form of French   Bois  ."]},{"name":"Baskerville","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Boscherville in Eure, France, named with Old Anglo-Norman French <i>boschet</i> ‘copse, thicket’ (a diminutive of   Bois  ) + <i>ville</i> ‘settlement, town’."]},{"name":"Debois","meanings":["Altered form of French   Dubois  , a cognate of 1 above.","French: topographic name, with fused preposition <i>de</i> ‘from’, for someone living or working in a wood (see   Bois  )."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":10,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas de Bois was born in 1280, in Deal, Kent, England, United Kingdom, his father, Edmund de Bois, was 38 and his mother, Mary, was 35. He married Margaretta Bonyngton in 1307. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1311, in Kent, England, at the age of 31."},"et":{"1280–1311":"1280–1311","1282–Male":"1282–Surnud","1285–Female":"1285–Surnud","1282–1311":"1282–1311","1307–1362":"1307–1362","1243–Male